231
00:21:29,370 --> 00:21:30,370
You see this kind of a humility, nonsensical.

232
00:21:30,370 --> 00:21:31,370
I mean, it’s alright, I mean it’s like
a ??

233
00:21:31,370 --> 00:21:32,370
saying, “Oh, how can I cure you?”

234
00:21:32,370 --> 00:21:33,370
It’s like that.

235
00:21:33,370 --> 00:21:34,370
It’s like no meaning.

236
00:21:34,370 --> 00:21:35,440
This kind of a humility has no meaning for
you.

237
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:39,380
“How can I do it, Mother?

238
00:21:39,380 --> 00:21:42,020
What can I do?

239
00:21:42,020 --> 00:21:45,789
Oh, I am no good.

240
00:21:45,789 --> 00:21:50,340
I’m of no use."

241
00:21:50,340 --> 00:21:54,679
This language must be given up.

242
00:21:54,679 --> 00:22:04,879
When it is ego then it is even worse.

243
00:22:04,879 --> 00:22:11,120
You can harm yourself and you can harm Sahaja
Yoga, at the extreme point.

244
00:22:11,120 --> 00:22:18,620
Egoistical people are extremely difficult,
they are such a drag, because they try to

245
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:24,149
do everything through their intelligence and
understanding and this and that, and such

246
00:22:24,149 --> 00:22:30,980
a rambling goes on and on and on, and you
try to pull them back again and they go back.

247
00:22:30,980 --> 00:22:33,809
It’s so boring, you know.

248
00:22:33,809 --> 00:22:34,990
Very boring.

249
00:22:34,990 --> 00:22:37,730
Because you know, I see the stuff, supposing,
I know this is it (a cup of tea) and I want

250
00:22:37,730 --> 00:22:38,889
you to have it.

251
00:22:38,889 --> 00:22:43,350
And between taking this cup to the lip, [if]
every time you are pulling it out, every time

252
00:22:43,350 --> 00:22:49,710
you are pulling it out, then how am I to take
it to your lip?

253
00:22:49,710 --> 00:22:50,919
It’s very boring!

254
00:22:50,919 --> 00:22:57,179
And this egoistical temperament is very prevalent
in the West, surprisingly.

255
00:22:57,179 --> 00:23:00,929
And I just don’t understand.

256
00:23:00,929 --> 00:23:09,640
They can take to all kinds of filth, all kinds
of perversions without arguing about it!

257
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:12,260
Just take to it!

258
00:23:12,260 --> 00:23:16,200
Any kind of perversion – “What’s wrong?”

259
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:29,070
But it is for them the most wrong thing is
to be accepting the fact that you are a Realised-soul

260
00:23:29,070 --> 00:23:32,880
through Sahaja Yoga.

261
00:23:32,880 --> 00:23:45,190
They’ll take anything else but not the truth.

262
00:23:45,190 --> 00:23:52,429
This ego is like a horse sitting on your head.

263
00:23:52,429 --> 00:23:59,730
You have to sit on the horse, and the horse
is sitting on your head.

264
00:23:59,730 --> 00:24:09,669
You are carrying the load of the horse – imagine!
what is the sense in such a thing?

265
00:24:09,669 --> 00:24:16,519
If you start analysing yourself, again you
will go into another trip.

266
00:24:16,519 --> 00:24:21,620
You have been such ‘trippers’ like [a]
Jack in the box, you see.

267
00:24:21,620 --> 00:24:26,769
Because you have been taking trips after trips,
there’s a sort of a spring.

268
00:24:26,769 --> 00:24:33,499
You try to see your ego, you go on a trip
of superego.

269
00:24:33,499 --> 00:24:36,070
You try to see your superego and you go on
a trip of [ego].

270
00:24:36,070 --> 00:24:42,020
I mean, a person who has been bouncing all
the time to this trip or that trip or that

271
00:24:42,020 --> 00:24:46,759
trip or that trip is just like a person travelling
all the time, doesn’t know whether he has

272
00:24:46,759 --> 00:24:49,019
to get down or has to go further.

273
00:24:49,019 --> 00:24:50,850
It’s like that!

274
00:24:50,850 --> 00:24:56,220
The habit of the mind is so egoistical that
you just take the ride on the thing.

275
00:24:56,220 --> 00:25:06,720
But the thing is [that] it is not that you
take the ride, but the ego takes you on a

276
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:08,409
ride.

277
00:25:08,409 --> 00:25:14,799
And whenever there is any such a thing coming
up, it grabs you.

278
00:25:14,799 --> 00:25:18,110
And the progress is extremely slow.

279
00:25:18,110 --> 00:25:37,570
Now the trouble with the Divine is that it
has its own protocol and if the King has to

280
00:25:37,570 --> 00:25:42,730
come to your house, you have to go and invite
the King.

281
00:25:42,730 --> 00:25:49,880
The King doesn’t write to you that, “Please
invite me to your house,” does he?

282
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:56,250
That’s why he’s King, after all!

283
00:25:56,250 --> 00:26:05,850
And he doesn’t implore people that, “Please
invite me."

284
00:26:05,850 --> 00:26:09,309
This Mr.

285
00:26:09,309 --> 00:26:19,441
Ego expects that 
you should be invited by the Divine.

286
00:26:19,441 --> 00:26:26,190
That the Divine must go out of the way to
fetch you out.

287
00:26:26,190 --> 00:26:47,029
Ego, in simple words, is nothing but absolutely
wrong ideas about one’s own value: by which

288
00:26:47,029 --> 00:26:53,580
you think that, “I am everything."

289
00:26:53,580 --> 00:26:55,970
What are you?

290
00:26:55,970 --> 00:27:01,590
Now don’t go on a superego trip.

291
00:27:01,590 --> 00:27:04,860
What are we?

292
00:27:04,860 --> 00:27:05,950
Nothing!

293
00:27:05,950 --> 00:27:08,740
We cannot even sprout the seed.

294
00:27:08,740 --> 00:27:18,860
Every day-to-day life you can see this clearly:
how ego jumps up.

295
00:27:18,860 --> 00:27:35,029
Supposing somebody says that, “British have
these qualities,” one feels very happy.

296
00:27:35,029 --> 00:27:39,230
“Oh, what a praise it is!

297
00:27:39,230 --> 00:27:41,600
What a praise for British!

298
00:27:41,600 --> 00:27:44,370
Oh, we are British!” immediately.

299
00:27:44,370 --> 00:27:48,790
Somebody says that, “British lack these
qualities,” finished!

300
00:27:48,790 --> 00:27:55,630
You are absolutely…then that person is the
worst person in the whole world.

301
00:27:55,630 --> 00:28:02,919
First of all, you must know that neither you
are British, nor Indian nor anything.

302
00:28:02,919 --> 00:28:08,639
You are just human beings.

303
00:28:08,639 --> 00:28:15,509
Ignorance is responsible for this ego.

304
00:28:15,509 --> 00:28:25,379
It is complete ignorance about yourself gives
you this ego.

305
00:28:25,379 --> 00:28:34,840
So once we are going towards light we must
know what are our hurdles.

306
00:28:34,840 --> 00:28:41,779
[This] is the preparation.

307
00:28:41,779 --> 00:28:47,799
Is the ignorance that we have about ourselves
that’s why we are going to see ourselves.

308
00:28:47,799 --> 00:28:53,580
And because of the ignorance, ego and super-go
both have come onto us, so at least we’ll

309
00:28:53,580 --> 00:28:58,049
have nothing to do with them.

310
00:28:58,049 --> 00:29:07,820
Supposing you have to go on the Himalayas
where you are going for an expedition.

311
00:29:07,820 --> 00:29:15,529
You are supposed to carry the lightest things
that you have.

312
00:29:15,529 --> 00:29:19,950
You don’t carry three luggage of tiffin
carriers, four luggage of this, and five things

313
00:29:19,950 --> 00:29:24,710
of that, to have a nice little bed there and
sleep over.

314
00:29:24,710 --> 00:29:27,730
All that you leave here.

315
00:29:27,730 --> 00:29:33,899
In the same way when you are going on the
expedition of knowing yourself, all that is

316
00:29:33,899 --> 00:29:41,139
loading up yourself must be put down.

317
00:29:41,139 --> 00:29:48,320
So again we come to ego and superego.

318
00:29:48,320 --> 00:29:57,279
Actually, these two are terrible elephants
which must be kept down on the ground.

319
00:29:57,279 --> 00:30:00,340
So we make our own study.

320
00:30:00,340 --> 00:30:04,830
These preparations are needed because we have
already gone on this side too much or that

321
00:30:04,830 --> 00:30:05,830
side too much.

322
00:30:05,830 --> 00:30:07,720
So the preparation is to bring you down, “Come
along here.

323
00:30:07,720 --> 00:30:12,860
Now you stand in the centre!” or we bring
you down here and stand in the centre.

324
00:30:12,860 --> 00:30:19,720
The preparation is nothing but is just to
bring you down here, that’s all.

325
00:30:19,720 --> 00:30:33,740
So with ego we move on and see what the ego
has subtler and subtler and subtler forms.

326
00:30:33,740 --> 00:30:42,790
Even in superego you have subtler and subtler
and subtler forms.

327
00:30:42,790 --> 00:30:51,299
To understand ego you must see what do you
plan about your life?

328
00:30:51,299 --> 00:30:53,690
It’s very easy.

329
00:30:53,690 --> 00:30:58,490
What are your plans about future life?

330
00:30:58,490 --> 00:31:05,909
To understand your superego you must know
what affects you very much, what makes you

331
00:31:05,909 --> 00:31:08,369
very unhappy.

332
00:31:08,369 --> 00:31:13,130
Or you can say, what makes you more happy
and what makes you more unhappy.

333
00:31:13,130 --> 00:31:20,710
Both things, happiness and unhappiness, are
the shadows of these two trees.

334
00:31:20,710 --> 00:31:25,830
One is ego, another is superego.

335
00:31:25,830 --> 00:31:28,389
Just watch yourself.

336
00:31:28,389 --> 00:31:32,659
What makes you very happy?

337
00:31:32,659 --> 00:31:34,369
Good clothes?

338
00:31:34,369 --> 00:31:36,080
Good living?

339
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:39,570
Or when your name appears in “Who’s who?”

340
00:31:39,570 --> 00:31:45,159
(book) or all such nonsensical things which
make you laugh, you see!

341
00:31:45,159 --> 00:31:46,629
All that.

342
00:31:46,629 --> 00:31:49,570
You just see that.

343
00:31:49,570 --> 00:31:51,470
What makes you unhappy?

344
00:31:51,470 --> 00:31:59,919
When [there is] some sort of a heartbreak
and this and that.

345
00:31:59,919 --> 00:32:02,580
All this kind of a nonsense.

346
00:32:02,580 --> 00:32:03,580
Both things are not yourself.

347
00:32:03,580 --> 00:32:04,580
They are just outside.

348
00:32:04,580 --> 00:32:11,950
So what is inside, if you have to find out,
first the outside must be taken away.

349
00:32:11,950 --> 00:32:20,230
If you have to taste the fruit you take out
the outside, you peel it out.

350
00:32:20,230 --> 00:32:27,059
In the same way, this must be peeled out.

351
00:32:27,059 --> 00:32:31,380
Now this you should see within yourself and
without also.

352
00:32:31,380 --> 00:32:34,489
You can see it very clearly without.

353
00:32:34,489 --> 00:32:36,009
It’s very easy.

354
00:32:36,009 --> 00:32:46,190
How you deal with others is the point – what
is your relationship with others.

355
00:32:46,190 --> 00:32:50,749
It is easier to know this outside than inside,
perhaps.

356
00:32:50,749 --> 00:32:58,460
When you talk to others, what is the impact
they have from you?

357
00:32:58,460 --> 00:33:06,540
Are you appreciated by others or not?

358
00:33:06,540 --> 00:33:08,239
Among Sahaja Yogis.

359
00:33:08,239 --> 00:33:13,289
Do you respect another Sahaja Yogi as a Sahaja
Yogi or not?

360
00:33:13,289 --> 00:33:20,090
Do you expect that whatever stage you are,
the other Sahaja Yogi will also come up and

361
00:33:20,090 --> 00:33:22,739
he must be given the due respect?

362
00:33:22,739 --> 00:33:30,980
Also you must see that when any Sahaja Yogi,
who has achieved something or who is at a

363
00:33:30,980 --> 00:33:33,539
better level, tries to pull you up – [do]
you like it or resist it or get upset about

364
00:33:33,539 --> 00:33:37,840
it?

365
00:33:37,840 --> 00:33:42,279
If somebody tells you, “This should be done,
that should be done,” do you take it as

366
00:33:42,279 --> 00:33:50,159
if he has abused you?

367
00:33:50,159 --> 00:33:55,919
If he is telling you about Sahaja Yoga you
should be thankful in all normal way.

368
00:33:55,919 --> 00:33:59,750
I feel thankful to you if you tell me something
that concerns Sahaja Yoga.

369
00:33:59,750 --> 00:34:00,750
Anything!

370
00:34:00,750 --> 00:34:04,580
Even if you tell me, “Mother this may not
be alright if You say.

371
00:34:04,580 --> 00:34:10,150
You see, the human beings are like this,”
I accept it and I do it according to your

372
00:34:10,150 --> 00:34:11,460
wishes.

373
00:34:11,460 --> 00:34:15,230
Or do you like it or not?

374
00:34:15,230 --> 00:34:17,820
This is how you will judge your ego.

375
00:34:17,820 --> 00:34:19,780
This is only your Mr.

376
00:34:19,780 --> 00:34:20,780
Ego.

377
00:34:20,780 --> 00:34:26,840
Actually, it is better to have another person
to fight your ego and yourself; both put together.

378
00:34:26,840 --> 00:34:33,480
If somebody tells you that, “This should
be done,” “Oh, I see, I have been doing

379
00:34:33,480 --> 00:34:34,480
that.

380
00:34:34,480 --> 00:34:35,480
Yes, alright.

381
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:36,600
You come and help me.

382
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:39,379
You pull me out.

383
00:34:39,379 --> 00:34:41,870
Work it out.

384
00:34:41,870 --> 00:34:44,430
Try and help me.

385
00:34:44,430 --> 00:34:45,990
I am horrible!”

386
00:34:45,990 --> 00:34:51,040
That’s the way, if you do it, [that] you
can get over this ego.

387
00:34:51,040 --> 00:34:54,630
But the other person should say, “You are
very nice.

388
00:34:54,630 --> 00:34:58,910
Alright, do what you please,” and then you
feel happy.

389
00:34:58,910 --> 00:35:04,510
This person is not so alright and you are
also not so alright.

390
00:35:04,510 --> 00:35:06,230
Because you have to pull out people.

391
00:35:06,230 --> 00:35:14,661
For example, if you understand that you are
in a crisis, you are in an emergency, people

392
00:35:14,661 --> 00:35:19,840
are getting drowned and some people are trying
to pull them out, they themselves are halfway

393
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:26,540
down, halfway up, they are trying to pull
you out, at that time if they say, “Hold

394
00:35:26,540 --> 00:35:28,960
my hand now!”

395
00:35:28,960 --> 00:35:38,980
If you feel upset about it then you are not
wise.

396
00:35:38,980 --> 00:35:43,570
Now in Sahaja Yoga there is no leader as such.

397
00:35:43,570 --> 00:35:47,140
I mean, nobody is appointed as leader.

398
00:35:47,140 --> 00:35:50,850
Anybody tries to do that, he goes down.

399
00:35:50,850 --> 00:35:57,590
But there is an innate leadership within,
and such a person is extremely humble and

400
00:35:57,590 --> 00:36:10,780
congenial and appealing and commanding too,
has to be commanding.

401
00:36:10,780 --> 00:36:15,360
And one should not feel bad at that time,
because if he says, “Go and steal something,”

402
00:36:15,360 --> 00:36:23,300
or “You go and join some- one of these nonsensical
things”, then of course he is wrong!

403
00:36:23,300 --> 00:36:27,530
But if he is saying that, “In Sahaja Yoga
you have to come up!”

404
00:36:27,530 --> 00:36:33,550
Even dominatingly (sic) if he says, I mean,
it’s a very good thing, I would say.

405
00:36:33,550 --> 00:36:39,790
Supposing somebody is in your neighbourhood
who is always criticising.

406
00:36:39,790 --> 00:36:43,490
In a way it’s a blessing because [if] there’s
somebody who is criticising us he’s trying

407
00:36:43,490 --> 00:36:44,490
to perfect us.

408
00:36:44,490 --> 00:36:47,230
I mean, we should take it.

409
00:36:47,230 --> 00:36:51,470
Not to feel bad about it.

410
00:36:51,470 --> 00:37:01,490
Supposing somebody is saying something about
you, if it is not true, then what is there

411
00:37:01,490 --> 00:37:03,980
to feel bad?

412
00:37:03,980 --> 00:37:10,240
If he is telling lies about you, there is
nothing to be frightened about.

413
00:37:10,240 --> 00:37:15,360
If he is telling the truth, then you have
to be thankful.

414
00:37:15,360 --> 00:37:19,810
Though sometimes the truth could be very unpalatable,
could be very, very bad.

415
00:37:19,810 --> 00:37:22,780
But it is a good thing.

416
00:37:22,780 --> 00:37:32,080
There is a saying in Marathi, “Keep the
house of the person who is a backbiter, the

417
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:38,600
one who backbites.

418
00:37:38,600 --> 00:37:45,610
Keep the house of such a man who is your backbiter
next to you.

419
00:37:45,610 --> 00:37:47,910
Next door."

420
00:37:47,910 --> 00:37:50,800
That you know your defects, you see, you correct
yourself.

421
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:55,150
Is the wise attitude.

422
00:37:55,150 --> 00:38:01,090
Because you cannot correct yourself, so have
a mirror by which you correct yourself.

423
00:38:01,090 --> 00:38:05,250
I mean, you should thank such a man that he
is criticising you.

424
00:38:05,250 --> 00:38:10,790
By pampering you if he is going to completely
destroy you, what’s the use?

425
00:38:10,790 --> 00:38:13,490
This is what the gurus are doing.

426
00:38:13,490 --> 00:38:19,190
They are all pampering you and destroying
you and ultimately you find out that you have

427
00:38:19,190 --> 00:38:23,390
been befooled.

428
00:38:23,390 --> 00:38:29,770
So if you accept the situation in which you
say, “Alright, if this is what is going

429
00:38:29,770 --> 00:38:42,090
to be the truth, it’s very much better for
my ego and if it is not the truth then what

430
00:38:42,090 --> 00:38:44,240
is so important?”

431
00:38:44,240 --> 00:38:59,370
This attitude helps in Sahaja Yoga very much,
a very wise attitude towards oneself is.

432
00:38:59,370 --> 00:39:03,460
And you will be surprised as you’ll grow
with this attitude, you won’t be easily

433
00:39:03,460 --> 00:39:05,890
hurt by what people say to you.

434
00:39:05,890 --> 00:39:07,060
You won’t bother.

435
00:39:07,060 --> 00:39:13,240
You know how much people criticise me and
say all kinds of things, argue with me, and

436
00:39:13,240 --> 00:39:16,190
I’m not bothered because I know they are
foolish.

437
00:39:16,190 --> 00:39:17,190
What is there?

438
00:39:17,190 --> 00:39:18,190
They are stupid people.

439
00:39:18,190 --> 00:39:19,190
What is there?

440
00:39:19,190 --> 00:39:20,940
Even if they praise me, what is it?

441
00:39:20,940 --> 00:39:24,310
After all, whatever they praise me is my nature,
nothing so great.

442
00:39:24,310 --> 00:39:26,770
See, it makes no difference.

443
00:39:26,770 --> 00:39:29,370
I am just watching my chakras working.

444
00:39:29,370 --> 00:39:30,810
I am not bothered.

445
00:39:30,810 --> 00:39:37,540
In the same way, it will happen to you and
you will not be bothered.

446
00:39:37,540 --> 00:39:41,540
But this will help your unloading.

447
00:39:41,540 --> 00:39:44,880
This will help your unloading.

448
00:39:44,880 --> 00:39:54,310
And, the unhappy part of it: in that we should
prepare ourselves in a way that , “Nothing

449
00:39:54,310 --> 00:39:56,950
can make me unhappy.

450
00:39:56,950 --> 00:40:01,670
What can make me unhappy if I am a Realised-soul?”

451
00:40:01,670 --> 00:40:08,720
Supposing you want to marry someone – take
a concrete thing – and you find the person

452
00:40:08,720 --> 00:40:12,750
has sort of misbehaved or you cannot marry.

453
00:40:12,750 --> 00:40:14,020
So what?

454
00:40:14,020 --> 00:40:15,920
“I am there.

455
00:40:15,920 --> 00:40:19,730
My value is myself I know."

456
00:40:19,730 --> 00:40:27,010
So your value, your self-esteem should be
such that nothing should make you unhappy.

457
00:40:27,010 --> 00:40:30,770
It’s all a drama going on.

458
00:40:30,770 --> 00:40:33,280
It’s all a drama.

459
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:39,960
But these things must be accepted by your
great intelligence because what I find here

460
00:40:39,960 --> 00:40:46,310
is the difficulty with the Western mind is
this that – it has too much of IQ, too much

461
00:40:46,310 --> 00:40:47,310
over-developed.

462
00:40:47,310 --> 00:40:50,120
